\f1\b0 \cf0 It is the current version of the OBIN system of prosodic features implemented by Michael Malt. To use it:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Create your Oracle Bundle with the other descriptors (pitch, MFCC, chromas)\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Save the resulting Bundle\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Take the resulting soundfile from the oracle and treat it with Sylseg_pipo_w_labels_016, press INIT and follow the steps :\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li1440\fi-1440\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	1.	}process the file (segments, wait for the end)\
{\listtext	2.	}chose Hertz\
{\listtext	3.	}chose the method between 3symb, 4EqSymb, 3Symb+slope\
{\listtext	4.	}chose the analysis type (Fundamental Frequency is recommended)\
{\listtext	5.	}do it ! (and wait for the end)\
{\listtext	6.	}save syllabe markers + labels in sec format.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\tx1133\tx1700\tx2267\tx2834\tx3401\tx3968\tx4535\tx5102\tx5669\tx6236\tx6803\li720\fi-720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}In the last step, one or several Text file(s) is (are) created that should be saved in the same area than the soundfile : I suggested to create a folder called Prosody_Text inside the folder containing the Oracle Bundle data.\
