\f0\b \cf0 Create_MIDIPitchSequence_from_Oracle
\f1\b0 \
This utility allows you to create a collection of MIDI data (notion and off) out of the detection made by the yin~when you ran the oracle.\
This is automatically done if you record from Max, but you can have older Pitch oracles where this file is missing. You can easily create it from the Pitch Datas.\
\
Just follow the indication from the program. The MIDIPitch sequence (actually a coll) is automatically created and saved in the right place.}